  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions. Typical legal definitions include:\n\n1. Core Elements:\n- Concealing the origin of illegally obtained funds\n- Transforming criminal proceeds into seemingly legitimate assets\n- Disguising the true source of financial resources\n\n2. Key Legal Components:\n- Intentional financial transactions\n- Funds derived from criminal activity\n- Attempting to make funds appear legitimate\n\n3. Typical Jurisdictional Approaches:\n- United States: Defined under 18 U.S. Code \u00a7 1956\n- International: Aligned with Financial Action Task Force (FATF) standards\n- Involves three primary stages: placement, layering, and integration\n\n4. Common Prohibited Actions:\n- Transferring funds with knowledge of criminal origin\n- Conducting financial transactions to conceal illegal proceeds\n- Engaging in transactions designed to avoid reporting requirements\n\n5. Potential Penalties:\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Asset forfeiture\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering definitions?",
